description: • Led events across 2 departments (117 subordinates; 7 divisions), during NAVSECGRUCOM's response to Naval Forces Europe's request in force reductions, major system transformations supporting world-wide SCI communications realignment, deactivation of legacy systems, shifting of mission responsibilities to elements of NAVNETWARCOM and ONI, and eventual organization closure. All actions completed 3 months ahead of schedule. • Coordination of events between all stakeholders maintained uninterrupted support, despite 50 percent loss of resources. • Proactively planned: SCI Networks deactivation - shifted to NAVNETWARCOM; TACINTEL and OPINTEL deactivated; NEWSDEALER, JWICS, SPINTCOMM shifted to ONI; SCI DMS activated under ONI; NEWSDEALER-In-a-Box (NIBS) activated, with migration to SCI DMS, under ONI; NEWSDEALER subsequently deactivated; training on the SCI DMS and NIBS prototype systems. • Improved maintenance compliance to 100 percent: equipment preventive maintenance, Asset Management System equipment accountability, accuracy and execution of a $395K annual budget, and established SSPs to exceed IA policy requirements. Identified software problems and forwarded local audit programs that were implemented throughout the NAVSECGRU. • As PSO, obtained 100 percent SCIF inspection compliance and DIA Operating Approval. Prepared Fixed Facility Checklists, Site Surveys, Risk Management Surveys and TEMPEST Addendums for new construction and modified SCIFs. Established SCIF files: FFC, accreditation authorization (physical, TEMPEST and AIS/ADP), inspection reports, operating procedures, alarm tests (IDS/IDE), Memorandums of Agreement and Understanding, and Emergency Action Plans. Initiated annual site inspections, semi-annual personnel security inspections, guard response force testing, and Executive Physical Security meetings.

description: • Responsible for a 500-item cryptographic and STU account. Trained 29 personnel as material users; 4 as Alternate Custodians. Supported 25 submarines. Improved mission readiness by taking control of additional voice nets and Intelligence Specialist shift work responsibilities. Developed Memoranda of Agreements to transfer responsibility for facility personnel to a single organization. Scheduled, assigned tasks, and tested an upgrade of the SI SSIXS suite that provided improved back-up capabilities.
